  <h1>My Account</h1>

   <h4>Logging in with Facebook creeps me out, what gives?</h4>
  <p>Have no fear! The Whoot uses only your most basic information from Facebook. And we only take the information once, not every time you log in. We think sites that take everything about you are weird. Below is what we use to make your experience on The Whoot so great.</p>

  <p>Facebook provides us with your Name, Picture, E-mail Address, Gender and Birthday.</p>

  <p>Here is why:</p>

  <p>Name – Other users need to know who you are<br/>
  Picture – A Picture helps people make sure they are following the correct “John Smith”. It also gives your profile a nice personal touch.<br/>
  E-Mail address – We need your email address for user authentication purposes. We also use it to keep you updated with activity on The Whoot. For example, The Whoot will send you a message to let you know when you have a new follower or if someone has commented on your post. (Please note that you can manage your email preferences on the Settings Page).<br/>
  Gender / Birthday – These are basic demographic data points we use to analyze our user base internally.</p>

  <h4>How do I change my profile picture?</h4>
  <p>You can navigate to your Settings Page by clicking the link in the top right underneath your Picture on your Main Feed. On your Settings Page you will see an option to change your profile picture.</p>

  <h4>How do I manage my notification settings?</h4>
  <p>You can navigate to your Settings Page by clicking the link in the top right underneath your Picture on your Main Feed. On that page you will see an area where you can manage the amount and type of emails you receive. </p>

  <h4>Can I change any of my other basic information like my name?</h4>
  <p>We get your name from Facebook, and no there is no way to change it.</p>
